Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of comparing similarity between trees, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and data structures. The paper also mentions the application of the algorithm to comparing contour trees of terrains in $\mathbb{R}^{3}$, which suggests a connection to computer vision and graphics. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves some combinatorial and optimization aspects, which suggest a connection to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the application to terrain analysis suggests a connection to cs.GR (Computer Graphics).
